                                <div class="breast-title">What is Liposuction</div>
                                <div class="breast-text">
                                    <p>Liposuction surgically removes fat cells from the body to create a slimmer, sleeker contour. Liposuction can be used for generalized fat removal to decrease your overall waistline, hips, and thighs, or can be used to target specific problem areas that are resistant to diet and exercise.</p>
                                    <p>Dr. Danielle Andry and Dr. Nandi Wijay, the plastic surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery (TOPS) in Houston, Texas perform safe and effective liposuction techniques to loosen, emulsify, and remove unwanted fat deposits. The procedure begins several small incisions in strategic areas to remove the fat precisely and efficiently. Your Houston plastic surgeon performing the liposuction procedure will then inject tumescent solution, which is a mixture of saline, a medication that decreases bleeding, and a local anesthetic to decrease postoperative pain. A cannula will then be used to break up the fat deposits for gentle removal. Once the fat has been effectively removed, the remaining fat cells are equalized to ensure excellent contour and symmetry.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div class="breast-clickbox">
                                    <a class="breast-click" href="/contact-us">book a consult</a>
                                </div>
                            </div>

