                <div data-jarallax-element="-150" class="text-section-box"></div>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Abs</h3>
                                <p>
                                    Whether you are a woman who wants to trim down her waist and create and hourglass figure or a man who wants more a more chiseled and defined six-pack, abdominal liposuction can help create the look you want.  The TOPS plastic surgeons  not only offer the more traditional surgical liposuction, but also perform Ab Etching to create the definition, contour, and illusion of six-pack abs.  Dr. Danielle Andry and Dr. Nandi Wijay all trained with some of the pioneers in ab etching liposuction and use techniques for a natural result.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Hips</h3>
                                <p>
                                    If you have excess fat in your hips/flanks/love handles, liposuction can help sculpt this area for a narrower, more contoured look.  This can really help cinch in your waist and give you that hourglass look.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Thighs</h3>
                                <p>
                                    The plastic surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery can perform liposuction of both the inner thighs and outer thighs as well as liposuction of the back or posterior thigh or “banana roll”.  Liposuction of the inner thighs can help give you a thigh gap and more contoured, muscular appearing legs.  Liposuction of the outer thighs can help continue that hourglass silhouette achieved with liposuction of the abdomen and hips.
                                </p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Arms</h3>
                                <p>
                                    Liposuction of the arms is commonly performed to decrease fat from the arm area.  The TOPS plastic surgeons also perform liposuction routinely as part of a brachioplasty or arm lift.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Pecs</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Pec Etching is a procedure that is becoming more and more common.  This procedure uses a combination of liposuction and, sometimes, fat grafting or gland excision to improve the definition and contour of the pec giving men a chiseled appearance.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-6 pt-lg-5">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Knee</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Surprising to many people, the plastic surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery commonly perform liposuction to the knees in our Houston patients to help smooth the lower leg contour and help the fat bulge above the knee that commonly occurs with weight gain and age.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Calves</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Liposuction of the calves can get rid of “cankles” and help create a more defined, muscular look of the lower leg.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Lower back</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    The plastic surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery can perform aggressive liposuction of the back to help improve back fat and back rolls.  This is critical to creating a smooth contour and can be a complete game changer for some of our patients.  The back is truly one of the areas of liposuction our plastic surgeons see the most dramatic results.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Neck</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Liposuction of the neck can be a powerful procedure that really sculpts the jaw and neckline giving a better angle between the neck and the chin.  This procedure can be performed in the operating room as well as in the clinic by our TOP S plastic surgeons.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Upper Back/Bra line</h3>
                                <p>
                                    Upper back or bra line liposuction is often essential to completing the look up lower back or 360 circumferential liposuction.  This can help remove upper back rolls and smooth back contour.  The plastic surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgeon commonly recommend upper back or bra line liposuction as an adjunct to breast reduction to help improve the contour and transition from the back to the breast area.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
